cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with using computer vision techniques to detect nodules in CT scans, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of adversarial attacks and synthetic nodules to improve the robustness and generalization of the detection system suggests that the paper may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of the conventional networks and stress-tests the false positive reduction networks, which suggests that it may also fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) categories.
